Package: cylcop
Title: Circular-Linear Copulae with Angular Symmetry for Movement Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Florian",
           family = "Hodel",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "florian.hodel@yahoo.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0099-1006"))
Description: Circular-linear data arise e.g. when describing movement with
    step lengths and turn angles, which are often correlated. This correlation 
    can be modelled using copulae. Turn angles are usually symmetric, meaning 
    that an animal has no inherent preference to turn left or right. 
    This package, which extends the \code{copula}-package contains Classes (S4) 
    of circular-linear, symmetric copulae, methods for density, (conditional) 
    distribution, random number generation, bivariate dependence measures and
    fitting parameters using maximum likelihood and other approaches. The 
    package also contains many methods for plotting movement data and copulae.
    Finally, we also provide an \href{https://cylcop.shinyapps.io/cylcop-graphs/}{app} that allows for interactive visualization 
    and exploration of all copulae in this package.
